title: undefined symbol: _ZNK6google8protobuf7Message11GetTypeNameEv on ppc64le
body_html:
I am trying to run the End-to-end AlexNet from PyTorch to Caffe2 on ppc64le.

I have observed the following error:

import onnx
File "<path>/lib/python3.6/site-packages/onnx-1.3.0-py3.6-linux-ppc64le.egg/onnx/__init__.py", line 11, in <module>
 import onnx.helper  # noqa
File "<path>/lib/python3.6/site-packages/onnx-1.3.0-py3.6-linux-ppc64le.egg/onnx/helper.py", line 13, in <module>
 import onnx.defs as defs
File "<path>/lib/python3.6/site-packages/onnx-1.3.0-py3.6-linux-ppc64le.egg/onnx/defs/__init__.py", line 7, in <module>
 import onnx.onnx_cpp2py_export.defs as C
ImportError: <path>/lib/python3.6/site-packages/onnx-1.3.0-py3.6-linux-ppc64le.egg/onnx/onnx_cpp2py_export.cpython-36m-powerpc64le-linux-gnu.so: undefined symbol: _ZNK6google8protobuf7Message11GetTypeNameEv

I have built caffe2 and pytorch using FULL_CAFFE2=1 option and I have also built onnx locally.

body:
I am trying to run the [End-to-end AlexNet from PyTorch to Caffe2](https://pytorch.org/docs/master/onnx.html?highlight=alexnet#module-torch.onnx) on ppc64le. 

I have observed the following error:
   ```
 import onnx
  File "<path>/lib/python3.6/site-packages/onnx-1.3.0-py3.6-linux-ppc64le.egg/onnx/__init__.py", line 11, in <module>
    import onnx.helper  # noqa
  File "<path>/lib/python3.6/site-packages/onnx-1.3.0-py3.6-linux-ppc64le.egg/onnx/helper.py", line 13, in <module>
    import onnx.defs as defs
  File "<path>/lib/python3.6/site-packages/onnx-1.3.0-py3.6-linux-ppc64le.egg/onnx/defs/__init__.py", line 7, in <module>
    import onnx.onnx_cpp2py_export.defs as C
ImportError: <path>/lib/python3.6/site-packages/onnx-1.3.0-py3.6-linux-ppc64le.egg/onnx/onnx_cpp2py_export.cpython-36m-powerpc64le-linux-gnu.so: undefined symbol: _ZNK6google8protobuf7Message11GetTypeNameEv
```
I have built caffe2 and pytorch using FULL_CAFFE2=1 option and I have also built onnx locally.
